<p>This a Introduction to Rails Project.</p>
<p>The data used in this project was obtained from a repository on Github <a href="https://github.com/FEND16/movie-json-data/tree/master/json">project.</a> </p>
<p>The second data source used is the <a href="https://github.com/stympy/faker">Faker.</a></p>
<p>The two files, top-rated-indian-movies-01.json and top-rated-indian-movies-02.json on this website were then stored locally.  </p>
<p>The were comibined and used for this project</p>

<p>In total , there are 7 tables for this project</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>Movie Table</p>
        <p>This table has the movie title,year,imbd rating,release date,story line, Image_id as the foreign key.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Actor Table</p>
        <p>This table has the actor name.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Image Table</p>
        <p>This table has the image link.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Director Table</p>
        <p>This table has a one to many relationship with Movies table.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Genre Table</p>
        <p>This table has the genres for all the movies.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>MovieActor Table</p>
        <p>This table supports the many to many relationship between Movie table and Actor table.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>MovieGenre Table</p>
        <p>This table supports the many to many relationship between Movie table and Genre table.</p>
    </li>
</ul>

